        <heading>1622.  Grandparents; causes for disinherison of grandchildren</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1622.  Grandparents; causes for disinherison of grandchildren
A grandparent may disinherit his grandchild for any of the causes, other than the sixth, expressed in the preceding Article, whenever the offending act has been committed against a parent or a grandparent.  He may also disinherit the grandchild for the seventh cause expressed in the preceding Article.</p>
        </content>
